Subject: Re: [T2] How long to cool down before adjusting valves

Hydraulics require a midrange of the minimum/max that the piston will 
move in the lifter. I once measured it around 2mm.  Adjusting cold will 
work fine if you are in the looser third of that range.

DurocShark wrote:
That's how I do the hydraulics on my 78. I learned from a trusted
  mechanic many moons ago with a Camaro I had, that "if ya' ain't
  burnin' yer knuckles, ya' ain't doin' it right."

